[Both Gujarat and Rajasthan States are located in the western part of India bordering Pakistan. They can be seen on the map at http://www.nationsonline.org/bilder/map_of_india50.jpg. Ahmedabad can be located on the map at http://healthmap.org/r/1iSU and Jaisalmer at http://healthmap.org/r/2Arb.

In the WHO malaria country profile for India (http://www.who.int/malaria/publications/country-profiles/profile_ind_en.pdf) Gujarat State has an annual incidence between 1 and 10 cases per 1000 population and Jaisalmer district, Rajasthan, and annual incidence between 10 and 50 cases per 1000 population. - Mod.EP]
